---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="INCI Ingredient Education — InciKorea">
  <div class="container py-16">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">INCI Ingredient Education</h1>
    <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Understanding cosmetic ingredients and why transparency matters</p>

    <div style="max-width: 800px; line-height: 1.8;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">What is INCI?</h2>
      <p><strong>INCI</strong> (International Nomenclature of Cosmetic Ingredients) is the global standardized naming system for cosmetic ingredients. It's designed to provide transparency and help consumers understand what's in their skincare products.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">How to Read an INCI List</h2>
      <p>Ingredients are listed in descending order of concentration. The first 5 ingredients typically comprise 80% of the formula. Water (Aqua) is usually listed first, followed by actives and then preservatives.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">Common Korean Beauty Ingredients</h2>
      
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; color: #0066cc;">Hyaluronic Acid (Sodium Hyaluronate)</h3>
      <p>A humectant that holds water in the skin, providing hydration and plumping effects. K-beauty often uses multiple molecular weights for layered hydration.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; color: #0066cc;">Niacinamide</h3>
      <p>Vitamin B3 derivative that reduces inflammation, regulates sebum, and strengthens the skin barrier. Beloved in K-beauty for its efficacy and gentle profile.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; color: #0066cc;">Peptides</h3>
      <p>Short chains of amino acids that support collagen production and skin firmness. Often derived from plant sources in K-beauty formulations.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; color: #0066cc;">Centella Asiatica (Cica)</h3>
      <p>Traditional Korean botanical extract with skin-soothing and barrier-repair properties. Trending in calming and post-procedure skincare.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; color: #0066cc;">Snail Mucin (Helix Aspersa Secretion Filtrate)</h3>
      <p>Natural secretion rich in glycoproteins and hyaluronic acid. Provides hydration and supports skin resilience. A K-beauty staple.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">Reading Between the Lines</h2>
      <p>Just because an ingredient is on the INCI list doesn't mean it's present in meaningful amounts. Look for positioning in the list — actives placed higher typically have better efficacy. Also check for supporting ingredients that enhance absorption or stability.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">Why We Prioritize INCI Transparency</h2>
      <p>At InciKorea, we believe transparency builds trust. Every CLUNA product provides a complete INCI list, detailed efficacy data, and honest discussion of what each ingredient does. No mystery actives. No proprietary blends hiding weak concentrations. Just clean, ingredient-forward skincare.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
